------------------------------------------------------------------------
Author:        AAVA       
Date:          
Description:   Conceptual data model definition for UTL and Resource Utilization Reporting
------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Domain Overview
The primary business domain is Resource Utilization and Timesheet Reporting, focusing on workforce allocation, billing, project assignment, and holiday/workday management across multiple geographies (India, US, Canada, Mexico, LATAM).

2. List of Entity Names with Description

2.1. Timesheet_New
- Captures daily timesheet entries for resources, including submitted hours, approved hours, and types of work (standard, overtime, double time, sick time, etc.).

2.2. New_Monthly_HC_Report
- Contains monthly headcount and workforce allocation details, including business area, project, client, and employment status.

2.3. report_392_all
- Aggregates resource, client, and project billing information, including billing type, category, and resource management data.

2.4. SchTask
- Represents workflow tasks related to resource allocation and project assignment.

2.5. DimDate
- Calendar dimension providing date, day, month, and year breakdowns, including working days and weekends.

2.6. holidays, holidays_India, holidays_Canada, holidays_Mexico
- Store holiday details for respective locations to determine non-working days.


3. List of Attributes for Each Entity (Business Names & Descriptions)

3.1. Timesheet_New
- Resource Code: Unique code for the resource (gci_id)
- Timesheet Date: Date of the timesheet entry (pe_date)
- Task Reference: Reference to the workflow or task (task_id)
- Calendar Date: Calendar date for the entry (c_date)
- Standard Hours: Hours submitted as standard time (ST)
- Overtime Hours: Hours submitted as overtime (OT)
- Time Off Hours: Hours taken as time off (TIME_OFF)
- Holiday Hours: Hours marked as holiday (HO)
- Double Time Hours: Hours submitted as double time (DT)
- Non-Standard Hours: Hours not categorized as standard (NON_ST)
- Non-Overtime Hours: Hours not categorized as overtime (NON_OT)
- Sick Leave Hours: Hours taken as sick leave (Sick_Time)
- Non-Sick Leave Hours: Non-sick leave hours (NON_Sick_Time)
- Non-Double Time Hours: Non-double time hours (NON_DT)

3.2. New_Monthly_HC_Report
- Resource Code: Unique code for the resource (gci id)
- First Name: Resource's first name (first name)
- Last Name: Resource's last name (last name)
- Job Title: Resource's job title (job title)
- Business Type: Type of business engagement (hr_business_type)
- Client Code: Code for the client (client code)
- Start Date: Resource's project start date (start date)
- End Date: Resource's project end date (termdate)
- Final End Date: Final end date for the resource (Final_End_date)
- Merged Client Name: Merged client name for reporting (Merged Name)
- Parent Client Name: Parent client or super merged name (Super Merged Name)
- Market: Market segment (market)
- SOW Status: Whether the client is SOW or not (IS_SOW)
- Gross Profit: Gross profit for the resource (GP)
- Employee Status: Employment status (Emp_Status)
- Employee Category: Category of the employee (employee_category)
- Project Name: Name of the ITSS project (ITSSProjectName)
- Offshore Status: Whether the resource is offshore (IS_Offshore)
- Subtier: Subtier company or group (Subtier)
- Practice Type: Practice or business unit (Practice_type)
- Vertical: Industry vertical (vertical)
- Client Entity: Client entity (client_entity)
- Portfolio Leader: Portfolio lead for the resource (PortfolioLeader)
- Status: Resource status (Status)
- Expected Hours: Expected working hours per month (Expected_Hrs)
- Expected Total Hours: Total expected hours for the period (Expected_Total_Hrs)
- Business Area: Business area (Business area)
- New Business Type: Contract/Direct Hire/Project NBL (New_business_type)
- Requirement Region: Region for the requirement (Rec Region)

3.3. report_392_all
- Resource Code: Unique code for the resource (gci id)
- First Name: Resource's first name (first name)
- Last Name: Resource's last name (last name)
- Employee Type: Type of employment (employee type)
- Recruiting Manager: Name of the recruiting manager (recruiting manager)
- Resource Manager: Name of the resource manager (resource manager)
- Sales Representative: Sales representative for the resource (salesrep)
- Recruiter: Recruiter for the resource (recruiter)
- Client Code: Code for the client (client code)
- Client Name: Name of the client (client name)
- Job Title: Resource's job title (job title)
- Billing Type: Billable/Non-Billable indicator (Billing_Type)
- Category: Billing/project category (Category)
- Status: Billing or project status (Status)
- ITSS Project Name: Name of the ITSS project (ITSSProjectName)
- Subtier: Subtier company or group (Subtier)
- Market Leader: Market leader for the resource (Market_Leader)
- Portfolio Leader: Portfolio lead for the resource (PortfolioLeader)
- Vertical Name: Industry vertical (VerticalName)
- New Business Type: Contract/Direct Hire/Project NBL (New_business_type)
- Requirement Region: Region for the requirement (rec_region)
- Client Entity: Client entity (client_entity)
- Circle: Circle or business group (Circle)

3.4. SchTask
- Resource Code: Unique code for the resource (GCI_ID)
- Resource Name: Name of the consultant or FTE (FName, LName)
- Task Reference: Workflow or task reference (ID)
- Type: Onsite/Offshore indicator (Type)
- Tower: Business or delivery tower (Tower)
- Status: Task status (Status)
- Date Created: Date the task was created (DateCreated)
- Date Completed: Date the task was completed (DateCompleted)

3.5. DimDate
- Date Key: Unique date key (DateKey)
- Date: Calendar date (Date)
- Day of Month: Day within the month (DayOfMonth)
- Day Name: Name of the day (DayName)
- Month: Month number (Month)
- Month Name: Name of the month (MonthName)
- Quarter: Quarter of the year (Quarter)
- Year: Year (Year)
- Days in Month: Number of days in the month (DaysInMonth)
- Weekend Indicator: Whether the day is a weekend (derived from DayName)

3.6. holidays, holidays_India, holidays_Canada, holidays_Mexico
- Holiday Date: Date of the holiday (Holiday_Date)
- Description: Description of the holiday (Description)
- Location: Location for which the holiday applies (Location)
- Source Type: Source of holiday information (Source_type)


4. KPI List
- Total Hours: Number of working days * respective location hours (8 or 9)
- Submitted Hours: Timesheet hours submitted by the resource
- Approved Hours: Timesheet hours approved by manager
- Total FTE: Submitted Hours / Total Hours
- Billed FTE: Approved TS hours / Total Hours (or Submitted Hours if Approved is missing)
- Project Utilization: Billed Hours / Available Hours
- Available Hours: Monthly Hours * Total FTE
- Total Available Hours: Monthly expected hours
- Total Billed Hours: Actual hours billed
- Onsite Hours: Hours worked onsite
- Offsite Hours: Hours worked offshore


5. Conceptual Data Model Diagram (Tabular Relationship Overview)

| Table/Entity             | Related Table/Entity        | Relationship Key/Field        |
|------------------------- |----------------------------|------------------------------|
| Timesheet_New            | SchTask                    | task_id <-> ID               |
| Timesheet_New            | New_Monthly_HC_Report      | gci_id <-> gci id            |
| Timesheet_New            | report_392_all             | gci_id <-> gci id            |
| Timesheet_New            | DimDate                    | c_date <-> Date              |
| New_Monthly_HC_Report    | report_392_all             | gci id <-> gci id            |
| New_Monthly_HC_Report    | SchTask                    | gci id <-> GCI_ID            |
| report_392_all           | SchTask                    | gci id <-> GCI_ID            |
| DimDate                  | holidays/holidays_*        | Date <-> Holiday_Date        |


6. Common Data Elements in Report Requirements
- Resource Code (gci_id/gci id/GCI_ID)
- Project Name (ITSSProjectName)
- Client Code (client code)
- Client Name (client name)
- Job Title (job title)
- Start Date (start date)
- End Date (end date/termdate)
- Status (Status)
- Category (Category)
- Subtier (Subtier)
- Portfolio Leader (PortfolioLeader)
- Vertical Name (VerticalName)
- Requirement Region (rec_region)
- Billing Type (Billing_Type)
- Submitted Hours (various timesheet hour columns)
- Approved Hours (various approved hour columns)

